Part 1: Project Backgroung¶

Nowadays, banking industries are spending a major part of its budget on marketing. To get best result banks need to optimise their banking strategies and for that understanding what their customer wants is necessary. This will also help them to make better marketing plans and design products that people actually need. This will not only improves customer satistfaction but also makes their marketing efforts more effective overall.

Main objective: Strategies to enhance cx engagement in bank's telemarketing campaign¶

This project will help bank to get know its customers better and create a profile for futire marketing. By analyzing customer features, such as demographics and transaction history, the bank will be able to predict customer saving behaviors and identity which type of customers is more likely to make term deposits. This will help to focus on those customers who has higher changes of getting converted. Moreover this with increase customer satistfaction by reducing undesirable advertisments for certain customers.

41189 rows × 21 columns

This dataset has 41189 observation. Each representing cx that the bank reached via phone calls.

For each observation, the dataset records 16 input variables that stand for both qualitative and quantitative attributes of the customer, such as age, job, housing and personal loan status, account balance, and the number of contacts. There is a single binary output variable that denotes “yes” or “no” revealing the outcomes of the phone calls.

In [37]:
count_age_response_pct = pd.crosstab(data_copy1['y'],data_copy1['age_bin']).apply(lambda x: x/x.sum() * 100)
count_age_response_pct = count_age_response_pct.transpose()

age = pd.DataFrame(data_copy1['age_bin'].value_counts())
age['% Contacted'] = age['age_bin']*100/age['age_bin'].sum()
age['% Subscription'] = count_age_response_pct['yes']
age.drop('age_bin',axis = 1,inplace = True)

age['age'] = [30,40,50,20,60]
age = age.sort_values('age',ascending = True)

plot_age = age[['% Subscription','% Contacted']].plot(kind = 'bar',
                                              figsize=(8,6), color = ('green','red'))
plt.xlabel('Age Group')
plt.ylabel('Subscription Rate')
plt.xticks(np.arange(5), ('<30', '30-39', '40-49', '50-59', '60+'),rotation = 'horizontal')
plt.title('Subscription vs. Contact Rate by Age')
plt.show()

Green vertical bars show that clients aged 60 and above have the highest subscription rate. Around 17% of subscriptions come from clients aged 18 to 29. Over half of the subscriptions are from the youngest (18-29) and oldest (60+) age groups.

However, red vertical bars show that the bank focused its marketing efforts on the middle-aged group, which returned lower subscription rates than the younger and older groups. Thus, to make the marketing campaign more effective, the bank should target younger and older clients in the future.

features = ['default']

    # Group by the feature and 'y', then calculate the count
    feature_group_analysis = data_subscribers.groupby([feature, 'y']).size()
    # Convert the series to a DataFrame and reset the index
    feature_group_analysis = feature_group_analysis.reset_index(name='count')

    # Prepare data for the pie chart
    labels = [f"{feature}_{y}" for feature, y in zip(feature_group_analysis[feature], feature_group_analysis['y'])]

    plt.title(f'Subscribers by {feature} and Y')

3) Campaign response rate

In [50]:
dur_cam = sns.lmplot(x='duration', y='campaign',data = data_copy1,
                     hue = 'y',
                     fit_reg = False,
                     scatter_kws={'alpha':0.6}, height =7)

plt.axis([0,65,0,65])
plt.ylabel('Number of Calls')
plt.xlabel('Duration of Calls (Minutes)')
plt.title('The Relationship between the Number and Duration of Calls (with Response Result)')

# Annotation
plt.axhline(y=5, linewidth=2, color="k", linestyle='--')
plt.annotate('Higher subscription rate when calls <5',xytext = (35,13),
             arrowprops=dict(color = 'k', width=1),xy=(30,6))
plt.show()

In this scatter plot, clients subscribed to term deposits are denoted as "yes" while those did not are denoted as "no".

As we can see from the plot, “yes” clients and “no” clients are forming two relatively separate clusters. Compared to “no” clients”, “yes” clients were contacted by fewer times and had longer call duration. More importantly, after five campaign calls, clients are more likely to reject the term deposit unless the duration is high. Most “yes” clients were approached by less than 10 times.

This suggests that the bank should resist calling a client for more than five times, which can be disturbing and increase dissatisfaction.

Conclusion¶

According to previous analysis, a target customer profile can be established. The most responsive customers possess these features:

  • Feature 1: age < 30 or age > 60
  • Feature 2: Education: more educated customer are likely incline to take term plan

  • Feature 3: Job: Cx with admin and blue collar job are majority in taking term plan.

    On the one hand, it will increase the efficiency of the bank’s telemarketing campaign, saving time and efforts. On the other hand, it prevents some clients from receiving undesirable advertisements, raising customer satisfaction. With the aid of logistic and ridge regression models, the bank can enter a virtuous cycle of effective marketing, more investments and happier customers.

Recommendation¶

  • Optimal Timing When planning a marketing strategy, it’s crucial to consider external factors like the timing of calls. Analysis shows that March, September, October, and December have the highest success rates. However, more data is needed to confirm if this trend is consistent. If it is, the bank should focus its telemarketing efforts during these months, particularly in the fall and spring.

  • Enhanced Marketing Design Targeting the right customers will lead to more positive responses, helping to correct the imbalance in the original dataset and provide the bank with more accurate data. To boost subscription rates, the bank should also review and improve its campaign content and design to make it more attractive to its target audience.

  • Improved Service Delivery Understanding customer demographics, such as marital status, occupation, and loan status, allows the bank to tailor its services better. This information helps predict when customers might need specific financial services, enabling the bank to meet their needs more effectively and provide the right services at the right time.
